The National Youth Development Agency (NYDA) is inviting young business owners (18 to 35 years of age) whose businesses have been negatively affected by Covid-19 to apply for their NYDA Youth Micro Enterprise Relief Fund. Funding would be kept at a maximum of R10 000 once-off grant, which the young business owners would not have to pay back. Applicants must be South African citizens. This fund is targeted at youth-owned businesses that meet the following criteria: The applicant must provide evidence of the following: Completed application forms must be submitted via email to the branch or district office closest to you. Click here to view list of offices.